                            <comment id="13597351" author="rjernst" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2013 18:02:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe this patch fixes the bug, but I have not figured out where the appropriate place would be to add a unit test for this setting.  Any suggestions?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601126" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 13:17:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;here&apos;s a test that fails without the patch, passes with it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601142" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 13:50:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried adding a .properties case just like the .xml case, but this one fails. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems to me something about the resource loading here is not right.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601171" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 14:15:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated patch: passing for .properties too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This had 2 bugs:&lt;br/&gt;
1. unlike the xml case, resourceloader was not consistently set, so it was null.&lt;br/&gt;
2. attributes and arguments for the plugininfo were wrong: instead of &quot;class=&quot; they were shardHandlerFactory.class= and so on, because the .properties prefix never got removed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601192" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 14:35:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;just added tests that arguments are properly passed to this thing in both xml and .properties cases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601354" author="erickerickson" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 16:56:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Robert! I&apos;ll be looking at this shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
